div2.p:
“Pish!” said Mr. Isaac Shelby, blushing like a girl;
                        “where would I have been if you and Moore and Findley and the rest
                        hadn't stood 'em off till we turned round?”

“I'm going away to Virginia, Davy,” he said;
                        “will you not go with me? We'll see Williamsburg, and come back in
                        the spring, and I'll have you a little rifle made.”

“Herr Gott!” cried Swein Poulsson,
                        from the bottom of a flatboat, whence he was tossing out venison flitches,
                        “four day, und vat is it ve eat then?”

“What a weird little piece you are,” he exclaimed;
                        “you seem to have wormed your way into the hearts of these men. Do
                        you know that you will probably never get to Vincennes alive?”

“And I would tell you one thing,” said he, with force;
                        “serve the people, as all true men should in a republic. But do
                        not rely upon their gratitude. You will remember that?”

“I should have had more faith in my old friend Gratiot, he said;
                        “but you will pardon me if I did not recognize at once the
                        statesman he had sent me, Mr. Ritchie.”

“You were right, Antoinette,” I whispered;
                        “whatever happens, you will remember that I am your friend. And I
                        will bring him back to you if I can.”

“You and David should like each other,” said Mrs. Temple;
                        “you are both capable persons, friends of the friendless and
                        towers of strength to the weak.”

“Madame la Vicomtesse should know them,” I interrupted;
                        and without heeding her glance of protest I continued, “It is she
                        who has cared for Mrs. Temple.”

“You will please to speak French, Monsieur,” she said;
                        “this gentleman does not understand Spanish. What is it you
                        desire?”
